text:
Have tried their nasi briyani before. Today try their prata for breakfast. Its nice and crispy. Curry sauce is savoury.
Worth eating.
$8 Mutton biryani, worth it! So yummy!

The fried chicken briyani was overall average once you account for the $7 price.

Rice was fluffy with spices being on the milder side. The gravy on the side and the achar were both on the blander side of the spectrum.

But the fried chicken batter was pretty tasty, albeit salty. The chicken was also chopped into chunks, akin to Hainanese chicken rice; so the bone bits were a bit annoying to deal with.

That was all to the dish, so the value isn't exactly there.

The chicken is tender ,rice is fragrant and curry is flavourful.
Hear the fried chicken is tasty. Will try that next time.
Order a plate of muton briyani, the price are $7 and I feel the price a bit on the higher side. Go try if you are near by the area. Q up for 25 min during lunch hours.
